<br>
&quot;Payback the nation,by what,killing a few centaurs?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If that is the case,I don't want any part of it. Theyre hardly a threat to me or you or even the nation. There are only four of them.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 388<br> <font color=#993300>(8/19/02 11:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Enemies</span><hr size=1> Alysia growled lowly at her reply.<br>
<br>
&quot;They are our enemies. I would understand your reply if you were against bloodshed, but you've proven that wrong in many cases.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turned back to the Centaurs and narrowed her eyes as they looked over a map of nearby amazon lands. By the Ancients, they still held that grudge about the stupid lands!<br>
<br>
&quot;Hardly a threat? To you or I, yes . .  but imagine that back in the village while all the other amazons sleep, these Centaurs sneek by and just happen to attack. What if they kill one of our sisters?&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked back at Zelia awaiting an answer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uiizeliaii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>II Zelia II</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#993300>(8/20/02 2:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Stopping a threat</span><hr size=1> Looking at Alysia<br>
<br>
&quot;If it's one thing I know,the tribes have been well protected lately,but if it pleases the nation...&quot;<br>
<br>
She stood up from her crouching position from behind the bushes,then rushes toward the centaurs. As she was running toward the enemy,those impalers returned at her wrists.<br>
<br>
As she came upon the first centaur,she lept over his back,and as she did so,her right impaler was drawn across his throat,slitting it wide open. She landed on her feet with a soft thud on the other side of the centaur as he fell dead.<br>
<br>
She looks at the 3 remaining centaurs,who seemed a bit surprised,but pulled thier weapons none the less.<br>
<br>
She looks at each of the centaurs,a dark smirk playing on her lips. &quot;I havnt eaten in weeks. I bet your human halves would make a scrumptious appitizer.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her smirk turned into a grin as 2 of the 3 centaurs now charged her,one on either side of her. Once they were close enough she lept straight up into the air,pulled off a tight front flip gaining some force,she then straightened mid air,feet coming down hard on the back of one centaur who was on the left. A slight 'Cracking' was heared when her feet made contact on the centaurs back. To her amazement,the force didnt break the back like she had hoped,just cracked it. The centaur she had landed on,immediatly bucked,and sent Zel falling to the ground and landing on her bum.<br>
<br>
Zelia rolled directly under the centaur now before he could start stomping. Quickly she swings both impalers up and across in an 'X' motion,slicing the centaurs belly open. She then quickly rolls out from under him before getting more than a splatter of blood on her,and before the centaur could fall on her.<br>
<br>
She looked up just in time to see the 3rd centaur right infront of her. The centaur starts trying to stomp on her with his hooves. She manages to roll from side to side,avading the first few blows,but not quite quick enough,and a pair of hooves comes crashing down toward her. &quot;Argh!&quot; She groans and brings her hands up,catching the hooves in her hands,and using that goddly strength of hers to keep the sharp hooves from coming down on her. She keeps a firm grip on the hooves as the centaur now tries to escape her clutches,but he fails of course,as Zel suddenly pulls then pushes up on the hooves,causeing the centaurs legs to separate,then the leg bones breaking.<br>
<br>
As the centaur screamed in pain,Zelia struggles to push the centaur back by his broken limbs,then releases him,giving her enough time to roll out of the way from the falling centaur.<br>
<br>
She jumps to her feet immediatly,a little out of breath,and looking from the cripled centaur to the 4th and last centaur. &quot;Bring it!&quot; She raises her voice some at the 4th centaur,who suddenly takes off running (hehe).<br>
<br>
Once making sure the 4th centaur was gone,she looks at the crippled centaur who was struggling,trying to get up,but failing miserably.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can forget the plans you and your commrads might have had.&quot; She stated simply,then began to walk back toward Alysia. As she was passing the crippled centaur,she swung her impaler,slicing the centaurs head clean off his shoulders.<br>
<br>
She stops just where Alysia is. <br>
<br>
&quot;Happy now?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#993300>(8/20/02 7:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Test</span><hr size=1> Alysia grinned as she watched everything play out before her. It was so real. She crossed her arms and then looked as Zelia approached her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Very impressive. You passed.&quot;<br>
<br>
She lifted her hand upwards and then brought it down. Each of the dead wounded Centaurs that lay there, quickly morphed into large white wolves. They all stood up and as their blue eyes began to glow, the blood dripped off of them and they nodded a bow to both amazons and darted back into the woods.<br>
<br>
Alysis turned to Zelia.<br>
<br>
&quot;You took something from the Nation, and for the Nation you attempted to give it back. This was a test. No one was killed. But I needed to see if you were willing to submit to the duties that protecting our fellow sisters comes with.&quot;<br>
<br>
She sighed lightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;If something like this had really happened, I would have jumped in myself along with you. One rule of the heart of us sisters, is we never leave eachother alone in a fight unless asked to.&quot;<br>
<br>
